 **Call ordering is load-bearing — the lease-handoff drill MUST run before quiescence, not after.** #147's chaos drill ([its plan §3.3 Phase 5](issue-147-compose-smoke-multi-experiment.md)) kills the lease holder *while work is still in flight*. If the library waited for quiescence first, the orchestrator would already have exited cleanly (it exits 0 when all held leases drain) and there would be **no held leases left to hand off** — the drill would assert against an empty lease table and silently stop testing the failure mode it exists for. The library therefore sequences `me_assert_two_leases → me_lease_handoff_drill → me_wait_quiescence`, and the wrapper examples below follow that order. The drill is responsible for ensuring there is still pending work when it kills the holder (the `MAX_TOTAL=2` cap leaves enough in-flight work that the kill lands before quiescence; if CI proves too fast, the drill gates on observing ≥1 still-`running` experiment before the kill).
 
-#### 3.1.1 Making the exp-2 host trio exec-mode-aware
+#### 3.1.1 Making the exp-2 host trio exec-mode-aware — dedicated `-2` overlays, mirroring how exp-1 already works
 
-Per Decision 1, the existing exec-mode overlays only patch the exp-1 trio, so the exp-2 trio needs its own exec-mode handling. Two shapes, in preference order:
+Per Decision 1, the existing exec-mode overlays only patch the exp-1 trio, so the exp-2 trio needs its own exec-mode handling. **The design is dedicated `-2`-trio overlays — symmetric with how exp-1's mode is already selected.** An earlier draft proposed an env-driven entrypoint wrapper (`EDEN_EXEC_MODE_2`) as the "preferred" shape; round-1 codex review correctly rejected it on two substrate facts:
 
-- **Preferred — env-driven entrypoint wrapper on the `-2` trio (a #147 coordination item, §11).** #147 already introduces entrypoint wrappers for the orchestrator/web-ui to gate flags on env. Extend the same mechanism to the `-2` host trio: each `*-host-2` service invokes a wrapper that reads `EDEN_EXEC_MODE_2` (defaulting to match exp-1's mode) and assembles the host CLI with `--mode subprocess` / the DooD flags / scripted as appropriate. Then a matrix cell selects the exp-2 exec mode purely through `setup-experiment` (which stamps `EDEN_EXEC_MODE_2`), and **no extra overlay file is needed**. This keeps overlay-file count flat and is symmetric with how #147 already env-gates the orchestrator. Requires #147 to land the `-2` trio wrapper-driven (or #183 to add it in wave 1).
-- **Fallback — thin `-2`-trio exec-mode overlays shipped by #183.** If the `-2` trio lands scripted-only and wrapper-retrofitting is undesirable, #183 ships `compose.multi-experiment.subprocess.yaml` (patches the three `*-host-2` `command:` blocks to subprocess mode) and `compose.multi-experiment.docker.yaml` (adds the DooD socket mount + `group_add` + `--mode docker` to the `-2` trio). Cells then layer e.g. `-f compose.yaml -f compose.subprocess.yaml -f compose.multi-experiment.yaml -f compose.multi-experiment.subprocess.yaml`. More overlay files, but clean layering and no #147 change beyond the base `-2` trio.
+- **There is no env-driven exec-mode model to extend.** Exp-1's mode is *not* one authoritative variable — it is overlay composition. Scripted ("host") mode is the base; subprocess mode is selected by layering [`compose.subprocess.yaml`](../../reference/compose/compose.subprocess.yaml) (which threads `--mode subprocess` into the host `command:`); docker mode layers `compose.subprocess.yaml` + [`compose.docker-exec.yaml`](../../reference/compose/compose.docker-exec.yaml). `setup-experiment` only accepts `--exec-mode {host,docker}` ([`setup-experiment.sh`](../../reference/scripts/setup-experiment/setup-experiment.sh)) — it has no `subprocess` value. A wrapper reading `EDEN_EXEC_MODE_2` would be inventing a three-state contract the rest of the substrate doesn't have.
+- **A wrapper cannot toggle the privileged docker-socket mount.** The codebase's deliberate security posture is that `/var/run/docker.sock` is mounted *only* in `compose.docker-exec.yaml` (stated in that overlay's header). A CLI-flag wrapper can't make a privileged volume mount + `group_add` appear and disappear — that is a compose-file concern by construction. DooD privilege must come from an overlay.
 
-The wrapper examples in §3.2 / §3.3 assume the **preferred** env-driven shape (exec mode selected via `setup-experiment`, `OVERLAYS` carries only the base + exp-1 exec-mode overlay + multi-experiment overlay). Under the fallback shape, each cell's `OVERLAYS` array gains the corresponding `-2`-trio overlay. The choice is the first thing wave 1 settles with #147 (§11).
+**The design (no wrapper):** #183 ships two `-2`-trio overlays that mirror the existing exec-mode overlays, patching the `*-host-2` services that #147's `compose.multi-experiment.yaml` defines (scripted by default):
 
+| Overlay (new, #183) | Mirrors | Patches the `-2` trio to |
+|---|---|---|
+| `compose.multi-experiment.subprocess.yaml` | `compose.subprocess.yaml` | thread `--mode subprocess` into the `*-host-2` `command:` blocks |
+| `compose.multi-experiment.docker.yaml` | `compose.docker-exec.yaml` | add the DooD socket mount + `group_add` + DooD flags to the `*-host-2` services (layered ON TOP of the subprocess `-2` overlay, exactly as `compose.docker-exec.yaml` layers on `compose.subprocess.yaml`) |
+
+A matrix cell then layers the exp-1 exec-mode overlay(s) **and** the matching `-2` overlay(s) — full symmetry. The `setup-experiment --register-additional-experiment` provisioning (§3.2 inherited from #147) must stamp exp-2's exec-mode-specific env (e.g. `_2`-suffixed cidfiles dir for docker mode); §5 notes this. The only #147 dependency is that its `compose.multi-experiment.yaml` defines the base scripted `-2` trio these overlays patch — no wrapper retrofit needed. This is **strictly additive** (new overlay files), so it doesn't touch the privilege-isolation posture of the existing overlays.
+
